                <img src="/upload/FAD/Ingresssbilder/Operaen_Fasade_100x75.jpg" alt="Facade of the new opera house in Oslo. Copyright: Jaro Hollan / Statsbygg" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/fad/whats-new/news/2008/magnificent-opera-building-officialy-han.html?id=506754" title="">
                        Magnificent opera building officialy handed over
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[04.04.2008]</p>
                <p>– The building won’t be any obstacle, Minister of government administration and renewal, Ms Heidi Grande Røys, said as she last Friday handed over the key to Norway’s new opera house to Minister of culture and church affairs, Mr Trond Giske. She was referring to the Government’s stated intention that the new opera should offer opera and ballet of a high international standard to a broad audience.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/fad/press-centre/press-releases/2008/clearing-the-pin-code-chaos-on-public-we.html?id=505957" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/FAD/Ingresssbilder/pinkalkulator_100x75.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/fad/press-centre/press-releases/2008/clearing-the-pin-code-chaos-on-public-we.html?id=505957" title="">
                        Clearing the pin code chaos on public web sites
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[03.04.2008]</p>
                <p>Users of public electronic services may look forward to a better future. The Norwegian government has decided to establish a public infrastructure – a common hub – for electronic ID (eID). This decision means that in the future citizens may use the same eID to log on to several public electronic services; the number of services will increase and the services themselves will become more advanced; there’s an end in sight  to the existing pin code chaos. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/fad/press-centre/press-releases/2008/norwegians-on-top-in-europe-in-digital-c.html?id=501620" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/FAD/Ingresssbilder/Digital_kompetanse.jpg" alt="Illustration of digital components. Copyright: Sunnyfrog, iStockphoto" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/fad/press-centre/press-releases/2008/norwegians-on-top-in-europe-in-digital-c.html?id=501620" title="">
                        Norwegians on top in Europe in digital competence
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[25.02.2008]</p>
                <p>Norwegians are more advanced users of the Internet than most other Europeans. Even though digital divisions still exist in Norway, according to new EU statistics the generation gap is smaller in Norway than in the European Union. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
